summary: Hot take: when Obi-Wan and Anakin do the swishy lightsaber tricks it’s not just for show, it’s the Jedi equivalent of the...
body: Hot take: when Obi-Wan and Anakin do the swishy lightsaber tricks it’s not just for show, it’s the Jedi equivalent of the cat-butt-wriggle that they do right before they pounce which is theorized to be them figuring out angles and distances so they can land right on their target. Same concept with the lightsabers.

summary: So, Star Wars’ clone troopers. I have an idea about them. What if they’re not actually decanted until they’re more the...
body: So, Star Wars’ clone troopers. I have an idea about them. What if they’re not actually decanted until they’re more the equivalent of a one-year-old rather than a newborn? Because newborn babies can’t really do much, but a one-year-old is much more developed. I vaguely remember reading something that said that humans are born prematurely in terms of development when compared to other mammals, which tend to be physically capable much earlier in their develpoment cycles than humans. I believe the reason given was that a baby’s head is so big in comparison to the birth canal that if birthing was left any later it would literally be stuck. But of course, if you’re decanted from a jar, that’s not nearly so much of an issue, you just make a larger jar. It would also mean that the Kaminoans don’t have to start caring for babies until they’re old enough to start learning things like feeding yourself and using a potty, which I imagine would appeal.
